      "y": 320
    },
    {
      "height": 600,
      "id": "76e0cbf3efc7e8ac",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "The discotech is fundamentally set apart from the rest of the game in a way I don't appreciate.\n\nNo other area in the game feels this way, and I anticipate that if I were to finish it, players would name this as the part of the game that starts to drag.\n\nIt feels like a breach of philosophy.\n\nI don't see my game's world fitting in with the concept of \"night life\" or moral grey areas.\n\nIt's also the only part of the game where the player must earn permission to advance, rather than simply advance.",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 720,
      "x": 14560,
      "y": -1460
    },
    {
      "color": "3",
      "height": 1010,
      "id": "a8e3f3e5a08b7327",
      "styleAttributes": {
