      "y": 80
    },
    {
      "height": 600,
      "id": "2ecc9f62b844c3b5",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "Late-game area, aesthetic scale needs to be greater\n\nNOT social, macabre, meaningless\n\nproductive, high-energy, industrial\nimportant, target for battery thieves\n\nnot overly-convenient that the player lives next door\n^^^ commercial, place of business that the player doesn't usually need\n\nplayer doesn't usually need, but is universally important?\n\nclean energy production facility?\nchandroid battery manufacturing?\n\na bit on the nose? why should the player live next door to this thing?\n\nI prefer there not being a power production facility. I prefer that being more decentralized or in the background.",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 820,
      "x": 15880,
      "y": -1460
    },
    {
      "height": 680,
      "id": "bd97a283294f7c4c",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "discotech side room (top floor)\n\n- [ ] elevator transport into room\n- [ ] room smaller\n- [ ] furniture\n- [ ] lamps\n- [ ] green walls\n- [ ] dark carpet\n- [ ] inaccessible doors\n- [ ] scannable air outside window \"too far of a fall, with your current equipment\"\n- [ ] building exterior\n\t- [ ] white seam\n\t- [ ] rooftop to fall onto\n\t\t- [ ] edges raised\n- [ ] spacey doors\n- [ ] nightclub walls\n- [ ] wall of monitors with gradients",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 720,
      "x": 16000,
      "y": -460
    },
    {
      "height": 480,
      "id": "84c6fbd437c77d95",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "whole game emphasizing joy of solitude\n\nkeep population to a minimum\n\n\n\nBut I want the player to go to a night club\n\nBut I hate night clubs\n\nBut I want a musical space with that night club energy\n\nBut I actually hate the night club atmosphere",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 640,
      "x": 16720,
      "y": -1460
    },
    {
      "height": 311,
      "id": "a34bd6205abef21b",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "uptown to supermarket exterior\n- [ ] looks like subway station\n- [ ] trains passing on side\n- [ ] bathroom doors\n- [ ] art deco style\n- [ ] tiles",
      "type": "text",
