      "id": "8ecb0caa57deb6ff",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "discotech lobby\nimportant to make this a high-trust setting\ndancer girls hug you, smiling\n- [ ] hostess girl standing at door, looking at you eagerly\n- [ ] elevator to VIP area\n- [ ] ~~statue of robot with handles instead of thug~~\n- [ ] door\n\t- [ ] red velvet\n\t- [ ] polished wood or plastic\n- [ ] pillar\n- [ ] walls\n- [ ] floor\n- [ ] ceiling\n- [ ] industrial door to switch",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 620,
      "x": 13880,
      "y": -700
    },
    {
      "height": 300,
      "id": "28807bdd2c0a5d4c",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "does having the girls dancing and showing off their bodies seem sleezy?\n\nWhat is sleezy?\n\nRemember, our current culture treats beauty and lust as profane things.\n\nThe only question to ask is if you're accepting that framing. Are you tying beauty and sex to profanity?",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 1160,
      "x": 14560,
      "y": 480
    },
    {
      "height": 100,
      "id": "cdfac187257db92c",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "is it dirty to you?\n\nno.",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 240,
      "x": 14560,
      "y": 840
    },
    {
      "height": 80,
      "id": "b088af8c3ed8f4eb",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "you do want a profound humanism, right? Man enjoying himself as man",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 880,
      "x": 14560,
      "y": 980
    },
    {
      "height": 360,
      "id": "dad50098ade337e0",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "What function is served by having these girls dance? What's actually going on when you look at them?\n\nI'm seeing their utter confidence and presence in their beautiful bodies. They're proud of themselves, and by virtue of them being there, they know they're beautiful. They're letting themselves be seen as objects of beauty.\n\nThe girls here are unafraid, free, open. They're skilled dancers and models.\n\nAnd the staircases up to the pedestals invites anyone to reveal and celebrate themselves in that way.",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 1160,
      "x": 14560,
      "y": 1320
    },
    {
      "height": 160,
      "id": "6bf041cda99c44b5",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "I think this line of thinking is rationalistic.\n\nMan *is* an animal. A rational animal, but an animal nonetheless.",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 660,
      "x": 14560,
      "y": 1100
    },
    {
      "height": 100,
      "id": "ed28490d8a46a4ac",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "remember that the jungle aesthetic ties fun to animalism and primitiveness",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 880,
      "x": 14840,
      "y": 840
    },
    {
      "height": 1000,
      "id": "63ef1ab095824464",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
